Probably my favorite "Turn Up for Brunch" spot. Even with COVID they had a  way of serving champagne for mimosas and you getting your food from their buffet, which all together was awesome. There's like 4 different juices for you to make your mimosas and the food was great.  My favorite thing about this place is the roof actually opens up (visible from the second floor) so you get some outside sun/air while you eat.

They’re charging a 4% Covid surcharge now. LOL what does that even mean???? I honestly have no idea what that means. Never heard of that but it is hilarious. I’m not sure why you would make this awful Covid pandemic the responsibility of your guests that ultimately go there to support your business during this time by charging a 4% surcharge.  What a shame.

The server Catia was amazing and my friends said the only problem they had was that they couldn't fit anymore food in their stomachs. All around a great time if you're into food and music that makes you want to dance. The bottomless mimosas didn't hurt either.

Came for st Patrick’s day. Place is absolutely empty. They charge you $20 at the door and we walk in and they said “you can hangout on the main floor but you can’t go go” there was 1 person on the main floor. Had to go back to the front and get our money back.

My friend and I celebrated our birthday with friends. Things started off great but took a turn. The brunch & mimosas were good. The music was awesome. The waiter was spread a little thin but she did a good job.  Everything was great until we went upstairs. We were standing near the side of bar when a waitress/bartender sprayed me with water and drenched the back of my dress, legs, and shoes. I was soaked. I turned around nicely and told her she sprayed me. As opposed to apologizing she was very indifferent and told me I shouldn't be standing there anyway. I asked for a manager.  Instead of him apologizing initially, he gave me a spill about how I shouldn't have been standing there and "that's what the rope is for", etc. Mind you the rope is facing the front not the side walkway which is where I was. I told him a simple apology would have been suffice. He apologized and sent us a round of shots of wine (why wine?).  Here's my biggest problem with what happened today: The waiter that drenched me walked over to me after everything was said a done and gave me a very dramatic and insincere apology. I looked at her and said nothing. She walked off then walked behind me and whispered in my ear "you did all that and wanted an apology and didn't even accept it, humph". This is not how you do business! She was out of line and the way the whole situation was handled should have been better.
I helped plan an event here and it turned out really great! The food and service was fantastic!

Go when they open and eat until they kick you out.  What could be bad about that? $25 all day mimosas, fresh delicious well cooked food and desserts, if you don't like something if you would rather have lunch, they have it all. When you have to give up your table, you can go upstairs and have a drink and take a plate with you. When we left, there was cotton candy in the wall on the way down the stairs from the club. A great way to start the weekend.
Music was lively, service was great and my friends and I had a fabulous time!

I had the time of my life at Fremont this September. My sister and I went on a Sunday for brunch and it was epic. The food was fantastic. There were oysters, shrimp, an omelette chef, a waffle chef, fresh fruits, desserts, and a smorgasbord of other options.  After eating, we went up to the second level to party. It was 11am and champagne bottles were being popped from every section of party like it was New Years Eve. The entry fee included unlimited champagne. It doesn't get any better than that. The we were several  DJ's that revolved throughout the day playing, Hip hop, top 40's, Afrobeat, dancehall, etc. They played all kinds of great music mixes and everyone hit the dance floor. Fremont is my favorite day party in Chi-town thus far.
I will have to say that the dancing seen was lacking.  The place was small and yet empty on a Saturday night.
Good Food, but too small

Had a pretty good experience dining with a relatively large party until we were leaving. We had a very attentive waitress who kept our glasses full throughout the day. Our experience soured on our way out as we were harassed by an employee and told, “we should leave faster” when the restaurant was closing. After correcting him, he continued to aggressively talk s#!+. In retrospect, I really wish I'd found out his name. After paying an $1800 bill you'd expect a much kinder level of customer service, but even if we paid $18 we were paying guests at this establishment and should have been treated as such.  This was my first visit and for the most part it was ok, but this will be my last visit. I phoned the restaurant to formally complain and never received a response. I believe in paying and tipping well to guarantee a great experience when I dine out. I am never ok with inferior service and/or power trips from unhappy, incompetent, poorly trained staff. I've told my friends and colleagues to take their business to HighLine on Kinzie. Both the food and service are 5x's better.

Although the food is great etc, the bartender upstairs curly hair blonde, tall at the bar to the left is extremely rude every time. This time she made my friend and I leave the bar as she was saving the sits for some two men who were not present at the bar. I understand if she is giving them special treatment whatever case might be, she could of have been nice abut telling us to leave our sits. I have not yet came across such an unprofessional, rude behavior at any restaurant, bar or club ...we will not be returning.

From other reviews, I can see many enjoy brunch at Fremont.  It just wasn’t for our group. The service was acceptable and friendly. At times the refills on sparkling wine were super slow but overall it was fine.  I’m not a fan of drinking Champagne out of a plastic “glass”. The water was in plastic and the coffee was in paper cups. I wasn’t at a picnic outdoors or poolside. Why can’t I have a real glass or china cup for my coffee?  The caliber of food for this brunch was not all quite up to par. A tortilla chips and salsa/nacho bar? Hot dogs and Italian beef?  The omelette station was great. The bacon was delicious. The carved turkey and sausage were very nice. The brisket was very tough and overdone.  It was very loud and not conducive to socializing with your group while dining. Not sure why the DJ and club music can’t kick in after brunch.  It wasn’t bad but it wasn’t great either. I wouldn’t go back.  I’d pay extra and go to Maple & Ash. Now that’s my kind of brunch.

I love the Fremont! As soon as we arrived the entire atmosphere was perfect for the Bachelorette party we were having. The mimosas stayed full as did our bellies and smiles. The food was AMazing! As soon as the Club scene started we were excited! The entire experience took a sharp turn as one of the bridesmaids had her Chase card declined for her bill and put on a security hold. She works downtown so was confused as to how this could happen. While she called Chase to solve the problem, the bus boys and waitress swarmed the table without really saying a word & spilled our drinks almost wetting the Bride! Of course the bride was upset it was very disrespectful. After attempting to contact Chase with no luck, there was quick pay  & a second bridesmaid used her card she uses in the area frequently & ALSO had a lock put on her card! After this we we're getting irritated as it was obviously the machine at the bar and the waitresses were pretty much pushing us off to the bartenders. Finally one of the girls withdrew money from the ATM there for an extra $7. Even after the terrible experience after brunch, we were courteous enough to tip 20%  & really enjoyed the DJ.

Me and my bridesmaid went to Fremont this past Saturday for brunch for my bachelorette party.  Once it hits about 12 noon the whole atmosphere changes into a clubish type atmosphere. The food was also great! So much to choose from! There was one bad thing that happened, you only get to sit at your table for 2 hours, which is fine. Well when it came time for us to move from the table about 2 bus boys and multiple servers came and just started abruptly and rudely grabbing everything off  the table! One server even spilled OJ all over the table and almost all over myself! They could have nicely told us that it was time to leave the table as we knew we only had 2 hours and that was fine rather rudely grabbing everything and basically saying get the f off the table! I was a server for  a long time and I would never do that to anyone, it was completely rude and uncalled for! I may return again but that really changed my opinion about the restaurant.
Love this place. Great food and drinks
It was good. Just wish there was more vegetarian options

Went to Fremont on my vacation with a group of friends for brunch. The atmosphere was rocking upstairs and the food selection was high quality and amazing. Special props to our server who had to deal with a belligerent crowd, got spilled champagne on, and was still pleasant and respectfull the whole morning. Would go again for sure on my next visit.

Went for the first time with a group of my friends to celebrate one of their birthdays, not knowing what exactly to expect but was overly surprised at what we saw. The place is very fancy looking with a delicious endless buffet. I pretty much tried one of everything and was not disappointed at all. The food was simply delicious! The dessert bar was too pretty to touch, but I did try something. The downstairs is more restaurant-like, while the upstairs is more club/bar-like, and the two complemented each other perfectly! The bartenders mixed drinks very well and I kept going back for more 🤣 We came from the northwest suburbs and found parking pretty easily at a nearby parking lot. Overall my friends and I had a great time celebrating her birthday!
Day party rooftop... I had a blastttttt, bottomless Mimosas and brunch

It's a typical pretentious Chicago establishment. I was there for an event and the doorman demanded me contact the host to walk me in. He wouldn't even let us go to the bar without a "ticket." Dude it's not that serious, it's a bar/ restaurant and this was at 5 pm on Wednesday. Get a grip.
Great place

Great atmosphere!! Great service!!
I went for brunch, more options for food would be nice.

After reading my review, PLEASE READ THE RESPONSE THIS PROFESSIONAL COMPANY SENT!!! IT SEEMS ITS NOT ONLY DOOR SECURITY THAT GETS AGGRESSIVE WITH CUSTOMERS! I AM DEFINITELY NOT A LIAR!!!  I was extremely disappointed during my last visit at Fremont on 6/30.  We are regular customers who usually sit upstairs in the booths next to the windows.  However, I will never patronize this establishment again.  Long story short, one of our guests were harassed at the front door, yelled at and threatened with gun violence.  He was also told that "his money is no good there."  This is despite the fact that we frequent Fremont and have spent a good deal of money there already.  The issue was that our reservation was under the promoter's name.  When our guest arrived, he gave the name of the person who made the reservations.  They made him wait in the rain until we came down.  By the time we got downstairs and tried to rectify the situation, door security was very disrespectful.  They would not listen to us at all!  There was one taller black guy and a shorter Hispanic guy.  I overheard the Hispanic door security tell his boss that "this guy doesn't know the name under his reservation."  Though we had already informed him of the promoter's name, he did not relay that information to his boss and made it seem like the reservation name was still unknown.  I believe at that point, he was irritated with the situation and took it upon himself to decide that our guest would not be coming in. After having to wait this out in the rain, the head of security came out and provided absolutely no customer service.  He started belittling our guest and threatening him with his gun.  The situation escalated and we ended up leaving early after still paying a $900 bill, leaving the first bottle we had just purchased and canceling the second that was on the way!  Our guest that received this treatment is a tall, black man who owns numerous LEGAL businesses.  I am not sure what kind of money Fremont wants at their establishment, but it was made clear that it wasn't his/ours!!!  I strongly suggest you get a head of security that does not prefer to incite anger.  In the times we live today, just about everyone has a gun! Bringing such a deadly tool up in a misunderstanding of words is extremely cowardly and unprofessional!  Management should never resort to THREATENING patrons with gun violence, especially when they are outside of the property!  Management should be trained to deescalate situations.  Lastly, just to reiterate, the comment about not needing "his type of money" was clearly racist to me!!  I find racism very saddening, but even more when it comes from another minority!  I will NEVER understand that!

Hands down, the most exciting brunch spot in Chicago. Be sure to have a reservation because the place fills up quick. The food is phenomenal! And the party atmosphere is great! This is the only place where I go to brunch in Chicago!

This place was so awesome. We felt out of place for the first few minutes but bartender Jessica took us under her wing and explained the whole process and it was great! Lots of tables are reserved but there was room at the bar. Keep your plate and silverware! Enjoy yourself and get the mimosas! We will be back as soon as we can. Not kid friendly really. Great DJ pumping upstairs! Seriously the fee is worth it for the in-house pastry chef's inventions alone. Recommend!
Their unlimited brunch is to die for. Highly recommend when you have an afternoon to spend just having fun.
Miranda was a gem!!  Treated my sister and I like queens.  Food was exceptional!  Brunch was perfection as well as those endless mimosas!!   I will be back very soon❤
Bottomless mimosas brunch in a club like atmosphere great for day party celebrations

Came for a friend's birthday back in December,  I know I'm so over due for this review. But I have been super busy! Had Melissa as a server and she was amazing. I've only experienced excellent service like hers 4 times in my whole life on Chicago, which is very sad. She was very accommodating and definitely will be the reason that I return. Also some drunk guys were harassing us and spilled a drink on me and let me tell you Melissa handle that so quickly and made sure that we were taken care of. She needs to start a class to teach other restaurants in Chicago customer service!!!

I had a great time with my family & friends. I would go again. The food was great & our waiter.
My friend took me here for my birthday it was really good the food was good the environment was good I would definitely be back

Let’s start off by saying we were seated at a dirty table. Most of the buffets hot food was cold. You have to serve yourself unless you get bottomless mimosa’s. The waitress are not real attentive. We had a party of 7, 5 people had the mimosas.Our waitress received a $86 tip and we don’t think she deserves it for refilling glasses hell we had to walk ourself over to the buffet to get the mimosa flavoring every time we got a refill. This place is over rated for a $40 brunch and $20 mimosas. Save your money no one gets that dam dressed up for breakfast or lunch.
Our waitress was great. But the menu was very limited and the food was not good.

Fremont’s is an awesome place for group brunch in Chicago. Their selection of food is overwhelming in a good way! They have everything from a donut wall to oysters! The bottomless mimosas were fantastic, the staff always makes sure you are topped off on champagne. Our server was extremely attentive and quick! The upstairs turns into a dance floor a little bit later in the afternoon which is really fun!

This place. This place was an experience. We went there for sunday morning brunch with bottomless mimosas, and it did not disappoint. The food was amazing and the venue was great. It definitely has the nightlife vibe, but was a great way to get your sunday started.

Today was my 1st time at Fremont and I must say this place was amazing. From the food, DJ, waitresses, an atmosphere. Came here to celebrate a birthday and this was a perfect spot. Unlimited mimosa and food. Arrived at 10am and left at 3pm. DJ AVI keeps you on your feet dancing the day away. I highly recommend this place and strongly suggest making a reservation because they do sell out Very Quick. Great Sunday Brunch! Amazing DJ!

The DJ had me dancing all afternoon! Great drinks and a good time for hip and urban crowd.
Fun bar, they have a really fun brunch thats great during the summer. Staffs awesome

Fremont was definitely a great experience for me and my friends the food was phenomenal always fresh prices is reasonable and the bottomless mimosas is a must. I highly recommend bobby as number One waitress both times she service me and my girls and both times we where pleased. She cool she fun to have and most importantly she love what she’s doing it shows. Thanks Bobby 😘

This place is basically a club with a brunch buffet. The mimosas are truly bottomless since you can refill them at the bar instead of waiting for the waiter to come check on you. The waffles were amazing! After eating we went upstairs to the club area to continue our bottomless mimosas. Somehow stayed there from 11-4 and had a blast. Definitely plan on going home and taking a nap afterwards.
We loved it! The food, the ambience and the atmosphere. Very modern, diverse and upscale classy.

First time at this place, sent a request for a reservation for a party of twelve,  Fremont RSVP sent me an email back with all of their options they offered for brunch, I thought that it was my confirmation for my reservation. And, to make sure we would have a spot for our party, I tried many times on different days to reach out to the reservation team with no response back. I left a voicemail to confirm our party a few days before Sunday and got no call back. But I had an email with our options for Sunday, and responded with what I wanted and at that point I’m assuming that my reservation was all set! WRONG! we arrived at the Fremont, and when we tried to check in; the hostess could not find my name in their system, I showed them my email to confirm that I did received a response from them. When they called the manager they informed me that there’s was nothing they could do unless there were cancellations in the next hour. While we were there we saw many empty tables, and told them we were flexible to sit in many separate tables, but we were told that was also not an option. Joe, one of the managers, took over the situation to made it worse with his attitude because he was unwilling to see that we had been trying to reach out for days with no response. I believe that Fremont could have done something for us in helping us get into the place in any spot but chose not to, the quality of the place should reflect on the poor management. All we wanted was to celebrate a special 40th bday for my sister, we left the place with a very bad impression from JOE the manager as he shrugged us off when we told him we were going to leave cause they weren’t letting us know of other options.

My first time at Fremont and let me tell you the food was amazing! The staff was really on top of the bottomless mimosas, my glass was never empty. I had a blast with my girlfriends. One thing that set me off and which I realized too late was what happened when I paid for everything. I'm not sure if this was intentional or human error but the barmen did not give me the right change which I was short $11 and my party left over $15-20 in tips separately. When I realized this I felt cheated and I wonder to how many people this has happened to since it gets so busy. One tip I have for everyone that goes for brunch and is paying in cash, COUNT your change!

Poor management they need to hire professional people for the money they charge, made reservations received a confirmation email when we got there they did not honor it. The minute we got there everything was bad, security guy not pleasant at all took my pocket knife (tool kit) and just put it in his pocket I asked him if he would be giving it back he replied “confiscated”

I was really excited to try this place with my family because the eleven of us were all going for the brunch and bottomless mimosas. We tried to make reservations online and the correspondence to get a spot was unhelpful at best. My mom tried calling 3 days prior to Sunday brunch and they did not respond to us at all. When we got there the manager, Joe, told my mom that we wouldn’t be able to get in and would have to wait to see if other parties canceled (that we’re coming an hour after the time we got there). He was very unhelpful and unaccommodating although there were plenty of tables available to sit in the VIP sections. We offered to split up our party to a few tables to make it better for them to sit us and they all told us no. While Joe talked to my mom he was very rude and told her that there was nothing he could do for us while all of the hosts stood there and talked badly about my mom and the situation. When my mom showed Joe the correspondence through email and proof of the calls, they said they couldn’t do anything about it. If you’re planning to come here with a large group and spend the money to treat your family to a boozy brunch, avoid this space at all costs unless you’re willing to pay to sit in the VIP section (which is obviously what they want).

I've travels to many places all over the world , and I can say without a doubt this is the worst hotel experience I've ever had . When you check in , you would expect no one would come into your room , but sadly , while we were out having dinner , the hotel staff came into our room and removed some items . There reasoning was flimsy  , and we were given a breakfast at the lobby cafe for compensation. ( oh boy !! )  ZERO STARS ...

After trying to make a reservation and showing up at the correct time, they told us our reservation was not correct. I called multiple times trying to confirm with no response. They were very unaccomdiating at all levels of management. Will not recommend

We went for brunch at 11am and fell into a time vortex that brought us somehow to 5pm. I can only vaguely describe what happened but I left with an overwhelming sense of satisfaction. There was food. It was good. There was champagne. It was also good. There was people. They were thoroughly entertaining. I danced. I chatted. I spent a good amount of money but every penny was worth it. Would I go back to the Fremont? Yes. Yes I would.

Best brunch in Chicago, hands down!! Went here for a friend's birthday and no one in the group has ever been here but we all heard good things. It is $40 just for brunch and an additional $20 for bottomless mimosas, but definitely worth the price. Everything from the omelet station, to the donut wall, to vegetarian options, there is something for everyone so if you leave hungry and/or too sober, that's YOUR own fault. Dress code is 'smart casual' aka NO SWEATS, dirty gym shoes etc. Basically, wear some nice jeans, a  cute top (stylish boots if winter) otherwise no basic gym shoes. It was only me and my husband and we did not make reservations. The hostess said they were completely booked but had space in bar areas upstairs and downstairs.
